The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | India men go down to US
                                                                                                                                                                                                     India men go down to US
                      
	Dresden: The Indian mens hopes of a podium finish went up in smoke after they lost 0.5-3.5 to the US while the womens team held France 2-2 in the ninth round of the 32nd Chess Olympiad.         
	With just two rounds remaining, the Indian men stayed on 11 points while the women inched to 12 points.         
	National champion Surya Sekhar Ganguly drew with Alexander Onischuk on the third board while Krishnan Sasikiran, P. Harikrishna and G.N. Gopal went down to Gata Kamsky, Hikaru Nakamura and Varuzhan Akobian, respectively.         
	The Indian women held higher ranked France thanks to a fine victory by D. Harika on the top board.         
	Harika defeated Marie Sebag on the top board while Tania Sachdev held Almira Cruikshank to a draw.         
	Nissa Mahouts also played out a draw on the third board with Silvia Coll but Sophie Millet ensured a draw for her team by beating Swati Ghate on the fourth board.         
	In an amazing turn of events at the top half of the table, Israel defeated overnight leaders Armenia in the mens competition while in the womens, favourites China were outdone by Serbia. Israel emerged as the new leaders in the open section on 16 points out of 18. (PTI)                                                                                                                                
